                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                <head>15. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="from">Kissinger</persName>) to Secretary
                    of State <persName corresp="#p_RWP1" type="to">Rogers</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d15fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 366, Subject Files,
                        Non-Proliferation Treaty (through March 1969). Secret; <gloss
                            target="#t_Nodis1">Nodis</gloss>. In a March 28 memorandum to <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>, Acting Executive Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_WJP1">John Walsh</persName> indicated that
                            <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName> would meet shortly with
                        Soviet Ambassador to the United States Dobrynin to propose simultaneous
                        deposit. (Ibid.) For a record of that meeting see <ref target="#d17"
                            >Document 17</ref>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d15fn2">In this memorandum, <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> told <persName corresp="#p_RWP1"
                            >Rogers</persName> that President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> wanted <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName>
                        to explore the feasibility of synchronizing the completion of ratification
                        and the deposit of procedures for the <gloss target="#t_NPT1">NPT</gloss>
                        with the Soviet Union.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1969-03-21"
                        >March 21, 1969</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                    <item>Ratification of the Nonproliferation Treaty</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has asked that you explore the feasibility of our synchronizing the
                    completion of the ratification/deposit procedures of the Nonproliferation Treaty
                    with the Soviet Union. If simultaneous completion is not feasible, the President
                    would like you to explore the possibility of completing the U.S. ratification
                    process after the Soviets have done so.</p>
                <p>The rationale for simultaneous action would be: <list>
                        <label>a.</label>
                        <item>The symbolic significance of joint U.S.-Soviet ratification for world
                            opinion and, especially, the hold-outs.</item>
                        <label>b.</label>
                        <item>Prevention of possible Soviet reservations to the Treaty after the
                            U.S. has completed its ratification action.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
